# Trivy CVE suppressions — each entry must document why it is accepted.
#
# Review this file when updating the base image or npm packages. Once the
# underlying fix is pulled in, remove the entry so scanning stays honest.

# CVE-2026-33671: picomatch ReDoS via crafted extglob patterns (HIGH)
# Fixed in: picomatch 4.0.4 / 3.0.2 / 2.3.2
#
# Affected location: /usr/local/lib/node_modules/npm/node_modules/picomatch
# This is picomatch bundled inside npm — part of the node:26-alpine base image,
# not a dependency of supergateway or server-memory.
#
# npm is not invoked at container runtime. It runs once during `docker build`
# (the `RUN npm install -g` step) and is otherwise dormant. No user-controlled
# extglob patterns reach picomatch during normal operation of the MCP server.
#
# Resolution: remove this entry once node:26-alpine ships npm with picomatch >=4.0.4.
CVE-2026-33671
